snippet.textDisplay:
Here is an HongKonger's guide to avoiding WARS (the coronavirus): (in no particular order)
1. Seriously, wear a surgical mask or a mask that can filter out bacteria and viruses like a N95 in public. Wearing the mask prevents you from breathing in the saliva/droplets of others which may contain the virus.
2. Go see a doctor if you are sick (and wear a mask). Do not just stay at home and hope that the sickness will go away.
3. Avoid people who have come back from China within the past 2 weeks at all costs. The virus has spread to every province of China as well as the main cities, inc. Macau and Hong Kong. Avoid physical contact with people.
4. Use hand sanitiser that fulfil WHO requirements, and soap that can kill 99.9% of all bacteria and virus, to clean your hands
5. Look out for people to cough and sneeze. It is more likely that the virus will spread through this way to others than by direct contact
6. Stay healthy by having a balanced diet, exercise, enough water and good personal hygiene
7. Drink water. It helps.
8. If you can, clean your phone screen.
9. Stay aware of the current situation regarding WARS. If you want an accurate number of cases or deaths, multiply the current number of cases by 10 or 100 then you will likely have the correct number. The PRC government has a long and extended history of fake news, so , yeah.
10. If you want more information on how to avoid catching the virus, other than youtube channels, official websites are fine, but also read the information from other places that are infected as they may have better unofficial guides.
Oh well, stay safe everyone!
